{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Project Runway'' contestants}}
''[[Project Runway]]'' is an American [[reality television]] show in which contestants compete to be the best [[fashion design]]er, as determined by the show's judges. The series first broadcast in 2004, and thirteen regular seasons and three all stars seasons have aired as of October 2014. The first five seasons aired on [[Bravo (US TV channel)|Bravo]], while the succeeding seasons aired on [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]].<ref name=PRNewswire>{{cite web|url=http://news.prnewswire.com/DisplayReleaseContent.aspx?ACCT=104&STORY=/www/story/08-21-2009/0005081305&EDATE |title=Lifetime Television's 'Project Runway' Becomes Highest Rated Premiere Ever for the Series and in the Network's History |date=2009-08-21 |accessdate=2009-08-21 |publisher=[[PR Newswire]] |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091001154001/http://news.prnewswire.com/DisplayReleaseContent.aspx?ACCT=104 |archivedate=2009-10-01 |df= }}</ref> ''Project Runway'' contestants are chosen by the show's producers through an application process that includes a videotape submission and "virtual portfolio" of sketches and completed designs, semi-final interviews at select cities, and a final interview.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bunim-murray.com/ProjectRunway_Application_and_Release.pdf |format=PDF |title="Project Runway" – Season 7: Application Instructions |publisher=[[Bunim/Murray Productions]] |year=2009 |accessdate=2009-08-25 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090521020025/http://www.bunim-murray.com/ProjectRunway_Application_and_Release.pdf |archivedate=2009-05-21 |df= }}</ref>

Two hundred contestants have competed, three of whom have competed twice—[[Daniel Franco]] competed in both [[Project Runway (season 1)|Season 1]] and [[Project Runway (season 2)|Season 2]] and Kate Pankoke in [[Project Runway (season 11)|Season 11]] and [[Project Runway (season 12)|Season 12]] in addition to Amanda Valentine in Season 11 and [[Project Runway (season 13)|Season 13]]. Angela Keslar and Vincent Libretti were originally eliminated in Episodes 8 and 9, respectively, of [[Project Runway (season 3)|Season 3]], but were brought back due to that season's twist. Justin LeBlanc would have originally been eliminated in Episode 6 of Season 12, but was given a second chance due to the newly instituted "Tim Gunn Save". During Season 13, the "Tim Gunn Save" was used to retroactively bring Charketa Glover back into the competition for Episode 7 after she was eliminated in Episode 6. Seven contestants left ''Project Runway'' for reasons other than being eliminated by the show's judges. [[Keith Michael]] was disqualified in Season 3 for bringing design books to the contest, which is prohibited.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seattlepi.com/tv/288881_tv17.html|title=On TV: A stunning 'Project Runway' season wraps up on Bravo|first=Melanie McFarland|date=2006-10-17|accessdate=2009-08-25|work=[[Seattle Post-Intelligencer]]|publisher=[[Hearst Corporation]]}}</ref> On the other hand, [[Jack Mackenroth]] of [[Project Runway (season 4)|Season 4]], Maya Luz of [[Project Runway (season 7)|Season 7]], Cecilia Motwani of [[Project Runway (season 9)|Season 9]], Andrea Katz of [[Project Runway (season 10)|Season 10]], Kooan Kosuke of Season 10, and Sandro Masmanidi of Season 12 all withdrew from the show due to personal reasons.

The 12 winners of the regular series are [[Jay McCarroll]], [[Chloe Dao]], [[Jeffrey Sebelia]], [[Christian Siriano]], [[Leanne Marshall]], [[Irina Shabayeva]], [[Seth Aaron Henderson]], [[Gretchen Jones]], [[Anya Ayoung-Chee]], [[Dmitry Sholokhov]], Michelle Lesniak Franklin, Dom Streater and Sean Kelly. The 4 winners of the All-Star series are [[Mondo Guerra]], Anthony Ryan Auld, [[Seth Aaron Henderson]] and [[Dmitry Sholokhov]].

