<sup>{{note|1|[I]}}</sup> Contestant's age at the start of the season<br>
<sup>{{note|2|[II]}}</sup> Angela Keslar and Vincent Lebretti were eliminated by judges during Episodes 8 and 9, respectively, of Season 3, but were brought back due to that season's twist.<br>
<sup>{{note|3|[III]}}</sup> Chris March was eliminated by judges during Episode 4 of Season 4, but was brought back to the competition following the voluntary departure of Jack Mackenroth.<br>
<sup>{{note|4|[IV]}}</sup> Anthony Williams was eliminated by judges during Episode 10 of Season 7, but was brought back to the competition following the voluntary departure of Maya Luz.<ref name=Luz>{{cite web|url=http://popwatch.ew.com/2010/04/01/project-runway-interview-maya-luz/|title=EW exclusive! Q&A with the 'Project Runway' contestant who quit the show tonight. 'I didn't want to be a one-hit wonder.'|first=Missy|last=Schwartz|date=2010-04-01|accessdate=2010-04-02|publisher=[[Time Inc.|Time Inc]]|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]}}</ref><br>
<sup>{{note|5|[V]}}</sup> Joshua Christensen was eliminated by judges during Episode 2 of Season 9, but was brought back to the competition following the voluntary departure of Cecelia Motwani.<br>
<sup>{{note|6|[VI]}}</sup> Raul Orosio was eliminated by judges during Episode 3 of Season 10, but was brought back to the competition following the voluntary departures of Andrea Katz and Kooan Kosuke.<br>
<sup>{{note|7|[VII]}}</sup> Justin LeBlanc was eliminated by judges during Episode 6 of Season 12, but was given a second chance due to the newly instituted "Tim Gunn Save".<br>
<sup>{{note|8|[VIII]}}</sup> Charketa "Char" Glover was eliminated by judges during Episode 6 of Season 13, but was given a second chance due to the newly instituted "Tim Gunn Save".<br>
<sup>{{note|9|[IX]}} </sup> Two designers have won the competition twice; Seth Aaron Henderson also won the third season of Project Runway: All Stars and [[Dmitry Sholokhov]] also won the fourth season of Project Runway: All Stars.

