'''Wanda Grażyna Gałecka-Szmurło''' (August 21, 1899 in [[Warsaw]] -January 10, 1993) was a polish lawyer, independence and social activist, the second woman in [[Poland]] who was entered on the list of lawyers.<ref>{{cite article|url=http://bazhum.muzhp.pl/media//files/Palestra/Palestra-r1993-t37-n7_8(427_428)/Palestra-r1993-t37-n7_8(427_428)-s132-133/Palestra-r1993-t37-n7_8(427_428)-s132-133.pdf|title=Szpalty pamięci: Adwokat Wanda Grażyna Gałecka-Szmurło (1899–1993)|last=Wojciech Krajewski|page=132–133|date=1993}}</ref> She conducted intensive social and journalistic activities in the field of law, she also participated in legislative works in the field of matrimonial property law.<ref>{{cite book|title=ZET w walce o niepodległość i budowę państwa – szkice i wspomnienia|last=Tadeusz Wacław Nowacki|publisher=Wydawnictwo Naukowe PWN, 1996.}}</ref> Advocate Wanda Grażyna Szmurło was appointed by the Minister of National Defense Janusz Onyszkiewicz (by order of 3 July 1992) a second lieutenant in the Polish Army.

